Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.58,0:00:03.65,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}As bright as a spark,\Nwith a sharp and precise wit.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.65,0:00:05.30,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Once he gets started, you can't stop him!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.30,0:00:07.13,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Stay right there for a sudden reversal of circumstances!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.13,0:00:08.98,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Today's episode has the smallest cast ever!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.98,0:00:10.82,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.82,0:00:12.74,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.74,0:00:15.05,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.65,0:01:40.53,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A car rigged with an explosive blew up at the home of the parents
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.53,0:01:44.45,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}of Megumi Sakihara{\rHonorifics - Narration Off\be10}-san{\r\be10}, a person who the old guy used to tutor in his school days.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.54,0:01:49.79,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The victim who passed away in the incident was Megumi{\rHonorifics - Narration Off\be10}-san{\r\be10}'s younger sister Hiromi{\rHonorifics - Narration Off\be10}-san{\r\be10},
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.79,0:01:52.09,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}who was backing the car out of the garage for Megumi{\rHonorifics - Narration Off\be10}-san{\r\be10},
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.09,0:01:55.01,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}because she was supposedly not good at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.55,0:02:00.39,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The suspect was a man named Hiromasa Takahashi.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.39,0:02:04.64,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He agreed to carry out an exchange murder with Megumi{\rHonorifics - Narration Off\be10}-san{\r\be10}'s husband Kazuo Sakihara,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.64,0:02:09.94,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}but he inadvertently kills Hiromi{\rHonorifics - Narration Off\be10}-san{\r\be10} instead of Megumi{\rHonorifics - Narration Off\be10}-san{\r\be10}.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.44,0:02:15.32,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Both men confessed to their crime,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.32,0:02:17.49,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and it looked like the case was solved. But...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.45,0:02:24.24,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}She backed out of a parking space that narrow...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.37,0:02:32.42,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}This case isn't solved yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.13,0:02:42.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}! What's gotten into you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.35,0:02:44.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, did something happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.76,0:02:46.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.56,0:02:50.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think Megumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} came here to buy us some cake or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.35,0:02:52.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's hurry and go to Megumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s house!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.98,0:02:56.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez. What's with that kid anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.57,0:03:00.36,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's too early to tell the old man about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.36,0:03:02.78,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I've got to get more solid proof.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.99,0:03:10.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I, uh... I just don't know what to say...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.83,0:03:16.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much. I'm fine, so please don't worry about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.63,0:03:18.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.92,0:03:21.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please have some tea before it gets cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.97,0:03:24.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.22,0:03:25.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll have some too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.43,0:03:27.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How about some cake, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.14,0:03:30.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.48,0:03:33.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,May I go to the restroom first?{lit. "before that, toilet where?"}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.41,0:03:46.37,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Over there...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.56,0:04:13.69,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Sakihara had a phone exclusively for himself upstairs
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.69,0:04:15.98,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and took all his calls with that phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.09,0:04:42.09,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.47,0:04:47.60,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's the remains of masking tape that was peeled off!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.97,0:04:50.85,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Just as I thought...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.89,0:04:55.27,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}So, "it" was set up there after all...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.90,0:05:05.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll bet you're relieved that Megumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} looked way better than you expected, right, Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.07,0:05:08.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I think she'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.24,0:05:12.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've got somewhere to go when we get to Beika Station,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.58,0:05:13.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so you can both leave me and go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.70,0:05:17.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right, but remember, don't be too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.48,0:05:40.57,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There's a window...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.11,0:05:44.24,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I see... If it's from that window...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.70,0:05:49.70,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Just as I thought...!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.08,0:05:57.92,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Okay! I've got the overall picture! Now all I need is proof!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.29,0:06:02.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm back!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.34,0:06:08.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Uncle...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.05,0:06:13.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something bothers me about the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.64,0:06:14.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.85,0:06:16.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because, remember Megumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} backed her car
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.98,0:06:20.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,out of the narrow parking space at the supermarket today, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.81,0:06:22.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then why did she have her younger sister back her car out for her
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.57,0:06:24.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,when the incident happened...?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.49,0:06:32.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, on the wall near the telephone of the upstairs study of Megumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s house,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.49,0:06:34.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it looked like masking tape was peeled off.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.79,0:06:36.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means that something was stuck on there, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.95,0:06:38.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Masking tape?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.38,0:06:47.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you know that there was a window way inside the garage
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.26,0:06:49.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,where the incident occurred, Uncle?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.68,0:06:52.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems that the window cracked from the impact of the explosion
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.14,0:06:54.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and a wooden board was placed over it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.35,0:06:55.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But with a window like that over there,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.81,0:06:58.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it's good because you can get a good view of the car from inside the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.48,0:07:02.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you trying to get at?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.06,0:07:07.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you insinuating that Megumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} has something to do with this case?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.69,0:07:11.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know. But...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.82,0:07:14.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't be ridiculous!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.20,0:07:20.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know her best because she used to be my student!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.96,0:07:24.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You knew her as a high school student, right, Uncle?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.55,0:07:31.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Megumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} could've changed after growing up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.09,0:07:33.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you dare get cheeky with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.05,0:07:38.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She hasn't changed a bit! She's the way she always used to be!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.10,0:07:41.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You want to believe that, don't you, Uncle?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.77,0:07:42.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.65,0:07:45.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But actually, she's already...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.19,0:07:50.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shut up and go on upstairs!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.49,0:07:53.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll go take a bath.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.95,0:08:04.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez! How dare that brat talk to me like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.25,0:08:09.63,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A secret window?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.43,0:08:15.30,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Yes, Hiromi and I call it that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.59,0:08:15.30,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Megumi During High School
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.22,0:08:19.85,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It seems that Dad actually wanted to use this as a door, though...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.81,0:08:26.65,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}When I was little and getting into things in the garage,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.65,0:08:29.32,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I would always be scolded from here...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.20,0:08:41.16,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Metropolitan Police Department
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.66,0:08:41.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The record of the testimonies of Sakihara and Takahashi?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.16,0:08:45.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. I'd like to take a quick look, and review the results.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.62,0:08:49.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did anything new come up in later investigations?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.30,0:08:53.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that you mention it, one of Hiromi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s friends told me
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.38,0:08:58.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that when Hiromi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was younger, she took two boyfriends away from Megumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.14,0:09:05.60,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Well, I guess you could say that she was very carefree...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.94,0:09:09.36,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It seems that Hiromi{\rHonorifics - Flashback\be10}-san{\r\be10} was only fooling around for the fun of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.36,0:09:13.40,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But it seems that when Megumi{\rHonorifics - Flashback\be10}-san{\r\be10} decided to marry Sakihara,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.40,0:09:16.16,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}although jokingly, she told her that if she did it again,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.16,0:09:18.62,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}she would make her pay for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.62,0:09:30.25,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Most likely, the old guy will find some sort of circumstantial evidence in his investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.25,0:09:34.76,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But when it comes to concrete evidence...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.02,0:09:50.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've got it! Maybe...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.82,0:09:54.94,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Inspector, about what I asked you over the phone a while ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.94,0:09:57.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I confirmed with Takahashi,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.78,0:10:02.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but the only time he saw her face was at that supermarket.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.91,0:10:07.12,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's the first and last time he ever appeared before Megumi{\rHonorifics - Radio\be10}-san{\r\be10}!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.12,0:10:10.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, how was Takahashi dressed at that time?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.29,0:10:13.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was wearing a jacket and sunglasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.00,0:10:15.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just as I thought!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.05,0:10:18.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, what are you up to anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.88,0:10:22.43,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Thank you very much, Inspector! Goodbye!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.43,0:10:24.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hey! Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.60,0:10:29.81,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Okay! Now I've got the proof!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.56,0:11:11.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? What do you mean? Hey, Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.44,0:11:14.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He hung up.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.52,0:11:17.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's the matter, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.36,0:11:21.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad's in Akihabara, and says he's about to go to Megumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s house.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.66,0:11:26.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said he's "the only one who can persuade her"...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.24,0:11:27.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder what he means?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.62,0:11:31.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}, let's go to Megumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s house too!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.08,0:11:34.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.04,0:11:37.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why'd you guys have to come too?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.76,0:11:41.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry. I was really concerned about your call.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.51,0:11:49.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry to keep you waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.68,0:11:51.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.40,0:11:56.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So what did you want to talk to me about?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.61,0:12:02.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Megumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}. I came here today to advise you to turn yourself in.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.82,0:12:06.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.42,0:12:19.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After finding out that your husband and your younger sister were having an affair,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.00,0:12:25.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,as an exchange murder was being planned between your husband and Takahashi,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.59,0:12:27.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you decided to use all this
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.81,0:12:31.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to kill your younger sister that you have always hated,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.14,0:12:35.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and send your husband to jail on charges of murder, isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.94,0:12:39.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad, what a thing to say!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.40,0:12:47.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Two months ago, you bought a wiretap and automatic recorder at a shop in Akihabara.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.83,0:12:51.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You asked the salesperson to give you the details on how to use the machines.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.41,0:12:58.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These are the same modular-type wiretap and automatic recorder that you bought!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.88,0:13:01.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't want to do it,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.01,0:13:05.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but when I went to the restroom a while ago, I checked out the upstairs study.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.39,0:13:10.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You rigged a wiretap to your husband's study
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.85,0:13:14.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and bugged his conversations with Takahashi.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.23,0:13:17.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The remains of masking tape peeled off the wall is proof.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.98,0:13:23.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were probably planning to listen to the conversation
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.86,0:13:25.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,between your husband and your younger sister at first, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.78,0:13:30.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But along the way, you found out something absolutely dreadful...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.49,0:13:36.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that your husband had agreed to an exchange murder with a complete stranger
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.92,0:13:40.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and that he had already killed the wife of that man...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.54,0:13:45.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The time came when it was your turn to be killed by that man Takahashi.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.72,0:13:49.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You found out that he was planning to rig your car with an explosive,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.68,0:13:51.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but was undecided because if he does so in front of your house
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.35,0:13:55.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,your husband Kazuo, may turn up as a suspect to...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.68,0:13:57.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you deliberately told your husband
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.69,0:14:01.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you were driving over to your sister's place,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.65,0:14:05.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,because her car just happened to be at the shop for inspection,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.19,0:14:08.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the garage was open.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.45,0:14:12.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your husband then goes out to a pay phone
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.91,0:14:15.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and tells Takahashi everything you told him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.00,0:14:18.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although you didn't listen to their phone conversation,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.58,0:14:22.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,almost positive that Takahashi was going to carry out his murder plan,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.92,0:14:24.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you went over to Hiromi's.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.21,0:14:29.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And after telling Hiromi that you were not good at backing cars,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.38,0:14:28.38,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Megumi's Parents' Home
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.34,0:14:32.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you made her back the car out of the garage for you
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.31,0:14:36.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As expected, your younger sister died.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.10,0:14:44.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But at that time, just one thing that you didn't expect happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.90,0:14:48.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I happened to come and see you!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.40,0:14:51.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were surprised and...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.03,0:14:53.03,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Wait, {\i1}Sensei{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.62,0:14:54.74,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.41,0:14:57.50,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10\an8}Alright, alright...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.12,0:14:58.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You wanted her to back out right away
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.25,0:15:02.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,because you didn't want me to see through your plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.01,0:15:12.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I did buy the wiretap, as you say.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.93,0:15:19.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I set it up behind the desk after suspecting my husband of having an affair.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.89,0:15:22.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I thought it over that night and immediately threw it away.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.77,0:15:24.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I didn't actually use it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.52,0:15:27.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you know that the person he was having an affair with was your younger sister?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.65,0:15:30.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had no idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.29,0:15:44.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's presume—this is just a presumption, now—that I did act as you had deduced,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.59,0:15:46.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,what crime am I guilty of?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.30,0:15:55.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takahashi is the one who rigged the explosive onto the car,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.39,0:15:57.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the person who put him up to it is my husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.10,0:16:02.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All I did, if anything, was make my younger sister get into a car
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.60,0:16:05.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that may have been rigged with explosives.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.02,0:16:08.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm not an accomplice in a crime, nor did I urge anyone to commit murder for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.65,0:16:11.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, {\i1}Sensei{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.86,0:16:18.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just as expected of a student in the law department, and a lawyer's daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.91,0:16:23.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just as you say,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.87,0:16:25.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,if all you did was get your younger sister to ride the car,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.79,0:16:27.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you wouldn't be found guilty of anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.17,0:16:28.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.96,0:16:29.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.80,0:16:34.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,in the case that you made your sister get in the car despite knowing
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.68,0:16:39.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that an explosive was rigged to the car, or if there was a good chance you knew,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.18,0:16:42.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you would be charged with homicide!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.77,0:16:47.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mentioned back then...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.61,0:16:50.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that you had to look for something, and went into the closet alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.24,0:16:54.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then you watched the garage from the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.86,0:16:58.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, just as expected, Takahashi came into the garage
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.12,0:17:00.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to set the explosive onto the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.20,0:17:06.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After you confirmed all that, you asked your sister to back the car out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.42,0:17:11.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, there was a very good chance that the explosive was
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.34,0:17:15.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,being rigged to the car, and you still made your sister drive it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.30,0:17:19.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you have any proof that I was watching the garage through the closet?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.39,0:17:22.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you do, please show it to me right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.56,0:17:23.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.81,0:17:30.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You've got proof, Uncle.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.78,0:17:35.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Remember? The sketch of the man that Megumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} said she saw,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.53,0:17:37.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that was drawn by police officer Honjo.{where is the translator getting this name?}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.12,0:17:45.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Megumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, where did you say you saw his face?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.83,0:17:48.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A-At the supermarket near my house.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.58,0:17:51.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? Strange. The officer mentioned that Takahashi
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.80,0:17:56.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,was wearing a jacket and sunglasses back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.13,0:18:00.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why is the man in the sketch not wearing sunglasses?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.68,0:18:11.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Megumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, you didn't even notice Takahashi watching you at the supermarket, did you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.69,0:18:18.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You found out only after you listened to Kazuo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s phone call that you tapped, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.53,0:18:21.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then where did she see his face?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.70,0:18:22.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From the closet!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.12,0:18:27.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She saw him from the secret window of the closet.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.89,0:18:49.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Megumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, you were watching Takahashi's face from the closet of your parents' house!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.81,0:18:53.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The face of Takahashi who was setting up the explosive!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.82,0:18:56.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-How can you be so sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.44,0:19:02.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That day, Takahashi didn't want anybody to notice him,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.20,0:19:05.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so he was wearing sunglasses until he entered the garage.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.58,0:19:07.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, he were his sunglasses when coming out too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.62,0:19:13.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But there was just one time he had to take off his sunglasses!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.21,0:19:19.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was when he was setting the explosive onto the car!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.30,0:19:26.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because nobody would even dream of doing a dangerous job
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.35,0:19:31.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,like setting up an explosive onto a car while wearing sunglasses
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.81,0:19:38.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, this sketch of Takahashi without his sunglasses is proof that
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.57,0:19:43.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you witnessed Takahashi rigging the explosive to the car in the garage!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.92,0:20:01.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just as you say, I happened to hear them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.22,0:20:06.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was planning to kill me and use the insurance money that I was covered with,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.56,0:20:09.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,along with the inheritance money my parents left for me,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.06,0:20:12.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to open a new boutique that Hiromi was to own...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.65,0:20:18.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, I remember the good old days...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.24,0:20:29.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was really happy back then...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.37,0:20:34.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I kept hoping that I could go back to those good old days all this time...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.13,0:20:39.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.63,0:20:43.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,15 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.80,0:20:48.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,there was something very important that I was supposed to have taught you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.06,0:20:53.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something more important than studying.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.27,0:20:58.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, maybe I can't really teach you much,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.19,0:21:02.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,since I'm separated from my wife and all now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.11,0:21:03.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,True!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.32,0:21:07.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it's not too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.41,0:21:10.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Repent for the crime that you have committed and study all over again.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.12,0:21:13.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This time, the study of life!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.29,0:21:17.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Will you watch over me... then again?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.34,0:21:20.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure! By all means!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.86,0:23:09.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's good that the case was solved, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.90,0:23:13.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This case must've really come as a shock to Uncle...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.33,0:23:23.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, Mouri Detective Agency...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.63,0:23:26.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.17,0:23:30.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A concert? Of course I'll go!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.55,0:23:33.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If for you, I'll go and cheer for you or tutor.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.64,0:23:35.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll do anything you wish! Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.56,0:23:38.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess we've got nothing to worry about.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.14,0:23:43.23,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Really! It takes the old guy no time at all to get back on his feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.69,0:23:48.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It bothers me! I met him somewhere,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.57,0:23:51.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but I can't remember where...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.28,0:23:54.66,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}An MO disc?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.99,0:23:57.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.75,0:24:01.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't remember buying this...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.87,0:24:04.46,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The old man who disappeared! The man wearing sunglasses!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.92,0:24:09.22,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Something... Something smells fishy!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.22,0:24:15.22,Signs,,0,0,0,,Next Conan:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.22,0:24:20.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint: Window glass
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.23,0:24:21.27,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Next time, a mysterious old man!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.27,0:24:23.23,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Geez, young people these days!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.23,0:24:24.31,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Is he the mysterious old man?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.31,0:24:25.44,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,No idea.
